europeMap.svg
=============

Source : https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Blank_map_of_Europe.svg
        (specifically the "with disputed regions" version at
        https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a7/Blank_map_of_Europe_%28with_disputed_regions%29.svg)
Author : Wikimedia Commons user "maix", based on earlier work by Tintazul.
License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported (CC BY-SA 3.0)
         https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/

This SVG is bundled as `europeMap.svg` with one local modification (see
below). It carries the original authorship metadata inside the file. The
CC BY-SA 3.0 share-alike clause applies to the SVG itself: any
modifications to `europeMap.svg` must be released under the same license,
and CC BY-SA also requires that changes be indicated — hence this note.

Local modification: added a small top-most `<path id="ax">` for the Åland
Islands (the island group in the Baltic between Sweden and Finland), which
the source map omitted. It sits on the existing island geometry so the
Europe map can identify and show Åland on click, matching the other
territories the asset already draws. This modified copy is released under
the same CC BY-SA 3.0 license as the original. The surrounding project code (JS, CSS,
HTML) does not become a derivative work merely by loading the SVG — this
is "mere aggregation," not a derivative, so the rest of the repository
keeps its own license.
